item.description:
Sending outputs to files Move into the folder example_files. We can see, for example, the first three lines of plants.txt with the command
head -3 plants.txt But what if, instead of printing the output to the terminal, we wanted to put it into a file? This is called &ldquo;redirecting&rdquo;, and is done with the character &gt;
head -3 plants.txt &gt; first_three_plants.txt The terminal will not give you any output, but what is inside the file first_three_plants.
